Package bio.singa.chemistry.annotations

Class Annotation<ContentType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • bio.singa.chemistry.annotations.Annotation<ContentType>
  • Type Parameters:
    ContentType - The type content of the Annotation.
    public class Annotation<ContentType>
extends java.lang.Object
    An Annotation in a chemical/biological environment is a relevant information about the Object that holds it, albeit not directly required for any application or method of this object. Certain AnnotationTypes are predetermined in order to provide a primary identification criteria. Further, any Annotation can be customized by setting a description such as "function", "is inhibited by", etc. (with setDescription(String)). Finally the content of an Annotation can be any Object. Every Object that implements the Annotatable interface can be given any Annotation.
